<html metal:use-macro="context/@@controlpanel_macros/macros/master"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      i18n:domain="aws.zope2zcmldoc">

  <metal:main-slot fill-slot="body">
    <p class="location-bar">
      <strong i18n:translate="">Namespaces</strong>
      <metal:to-english-macro
         use-macro="context/@@controlpanel_macros/macros/to_english" />
    </p>
    <ul>
      <tal:loop repeat="ns view/namespaces">
        <li>
          <a href="#"
             tal:attributes="href ns/view_url"
             tal:content="ns/namespace_url">
            http://namespaces.zope.org/some_ns
          </a>
        </li>
      </tal:loop>
    </ul>
    <hr />
    <h4 i18n:translate="">Important notes:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li i18n:translate="important_note_1">
        With Zope 2.12 and earlier versions, we do not and can not provide the
        documentation of directives of the <strong>'zcml'</strong> namespace
        (http://namespaces.zope.org/zcml). It's built-in nature does not provide
        the required reflectivity.
      </li>
      <li i18n:translate="important_note_2">
        Potential errors or typos in directive descriptions are not 'issues' of
        'aws.zope2zcmldoc' component, as we display the docs that are provided by
        these directives definitions. Please report these issues to the author of
        the component that provides the ZCML directive.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </metal:main-slot>
</html>
